# Exp 1 A' general
fit.1 <- lmer(Sensitivity_tot ~ Area + (1|Subject), data = DRM_1)

anova(fit.1)
## Type III Analysis of Variance Table with Satterthwaite's method

# Exp 1 B''D general
fit.2 <- lmer(Bias_tot ~ Area + (1|Subject), data = DRM_1)

anova(fit.2)
## Type III Analysis of Variance Table with Satterthwaite's method
##        Sum Sq  Mean Sq NumDF DenDF F value Pr(>F)
## Area 0.047428 0.047428     1    23  1.1014 0.3049
# Exp 1 A' dividing in critical lures vs unrelated words

fit.3 <- lmer(Sensitivity ~ Area * Type + (1|Subject), data = DRM_1)

anova(fit.3)
## Type III Analysis of Variance Table with Satterthwaite's method
##            Sum Sq Mean Sq NumDF DenDF F value    Pr(>F)    
## Area      0.05067 0.05067     1    69  2.5336   0.11601    
## Type      1.95281 1.95281     1    69 97.6365 7.621e-15 ***
## Area:Type 0.07941 0.07941     1    69  3.9705   0.05026 .  
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
fit.3.1 <- emmeans(fit.3, pairwise ~ Area|Type, adjust = "none")
summary(fit.3.1, type = "response")
## $emmeans
## Type = Critical_lure:
##  Area emmean     SE   df lower.CL upper.CL
##  cedx  0.557 0.0392 56.5    0.478    0.635
##  cz    0.660 0.0392 56.5    0.582    0.739
## 
## Type = Unrelated:
##  Area emmean     SE   df lower.CL upper.CL
##  cedx  0.900 0.0392 56.5    0.821    0.978
##  cz    0.888 0.0392 56.5    0.810    0.967
## 
## Degrees-of-freedom method: kenward-roger 
## Confidence level used: 0.95 
## 
## $contrasts
## Type = Critical_lure:
##  contrast  estimate     SE df t.ratio p.value
##  cedx - cz  -0.1035 0.0408 69 -2.535  0.0135 
## 
## Type = Unrelated:
##  contrast  estimate     SE df t.ratio p.value
##  cedx - cz   0.0116 0.0408 69  0.283  0.7777 
## 
## Degrees-of-freedom method: kenward-roger
e3 <- allEffects(fit.3)
print(e3)
##  model: Sensitivity ~ Area * Type
## 
##  Area*Type effect
##       Type
## Area   Critical_lure Unrelated
##   cedx     0.5569803 0.8997525
##   cz       0.6604540 0.8881800
plot(e3, rug = F, grid = T, multiline = T, ci.style = 'auto')

# Exp 2 on raw data

REL2 <- read.csv2("Google Drive/1_PhD/1_progetti/6_semantics/freq/NW_freq.csv",header=T,sep=";",dec=",",fill = T)

DRM_2_raw2 <- merge(DRM_2_raw,REL2)

DRM_2_raw2 <- subset(DRM_2_raw2, Type.N < 4)

fit.10 <- glmer(resp_resp ~ Area * DSM.9.raw + (1|Subject) + (1|word), data = DRM_2_raw2, family = binomial, control=glmerControl(optimizer="bobyqa",optCtrl=list(maxfun=2e5)))

summ(fit.10)
## MODEL INFO:
## Observations: 2560
## Dependent Variable: resp_resp
## Type: Mixed effects generalized linear regression
## Error Distribution: binomial
## Link function: logit 
## 
## MODEL FIT:

## Pseudo-R (fixed effects) = 0.19
## Pseudo-R (total) = 0.54 
## 
## FIXED EFFECTS:

## ---------------------- ------- ------ -------- ------

## Areacz                    0.19   0.20     0.93   0.35
## DSM.9.raw                14.17   1.90     7.44   0.00
## Areacz:DSM.9.raw         -2.55   1.29    -1.97   0.05

plot(e10,multiline=TRUE,confint=TRUE,ci.style="bands",type="response",rug=F,grid=T)
